  "prompt": "How many women are FDNY firefighters?",
  "response": "As of the latest available data, the number of women serving as firefighters in the Fire Department of New York (FDNY) is relatively small but has been gradually increasing. Historically, the FDNY has been predominantly male, but efforts have been made to recruit and retain more women. \n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date statistics, it is best to refer directly to the FDNY or recent official reports. In recent years, the percentage of women in the FDNY has been around 1% to 2% of the total firefighting force. For example, as of 2020, there were approximately 70 to 80 women serving as firefighters out of a total of around 11,000 firefighters.\n\nFor the most precise figures, consulting the FDNY's official website or their recruitment and diversity reports would provide the latest information.",
